# Template Governance Contract

## Purpose
Define non-visual governance for template-first page generation:
- where AI may edit
- what must remain locked
- how pages are derived from templates

This contract governs workflow and boundaries, not visual layout heuristics.

---

## Editing Boundaries (Hard Constraint)

AI MUST:
- Start each page from an existing template under `src/layout/templates/`.
- Build page output in `src/pages/`.
- Preserve locked template regions/components exactly as authored.

AI MUST NOT:
- Modify or replace locked pattern regions (e.g., global header, title bar) unless explicitly requested.
- Reorder locked template sections.
- Introduce alternate page frameworks outside the template model.

---

## Locked Marker Rule

Any JSX node marked with `data-region-lock="locked"` is uneditable by default.
AI MUST NOT modify, remove, replace, or reorder locked nodes unless the user explicitly requests it.

---

## Page Derivation Rules

AI MUST:
- Create or update page modules in `src/pages/` as template-derived outputs.
- Keep app-level wiring files minimal and focused on mounting pages.
- Follow `component-usage.mdc` for component source restrictions.
- Follow `layout-heuristics.mdc` for visual composition choices.

AI MUST NOT:
- Author page content directly in template source files unless explicitly requested.
- Bypass template structure by building standalone ad hoc page scaffolds.

---

## Scope

Applies to AI-authored page generation and edits in:
- `src/pages/`
- template sources in `src/layout/templates/` (as reference/locked scaffolding)
